   <span class="mw-editsection-divider">
    |
   </span>
   <a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-2" title="Edit section: ">
    edit source
   </a>
   <span class="mw-editsection-bracket">
    ]
   </span>
  </span>
 </h2>
 <p>
  <a class="image" onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);">
   <img alt="cdferwp201801 image4.png" data-file-height="784" data-file-width="1736" height="406" src="/mediawiki/images/thumb/7/7f/cdferwp201801_image4.png/900px-cdferwp201801_image4.png" srcset="/mediawiki/images/thumb/7/7f/cdferwp201801_image4.png/1350px-cdferwp201801_image4.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/7/7f/cdferwp201801_image4.png 2x" width="900"/>
  </a>
 </p>
 <h2>
  <span class="mw-headline" id="Standards_and_policies">
   Standards and policies
  </span>
  <span class="mw-editsection">
   <span class="mw-editsection-bracket">
    [
   </span>
   <a class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-3" title="Edit section: ">
    edit
   </a>
   <span class="mw-editsection-divider">
    |
   </span>
   <a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-3" title="Edit section: ">
    edit source
   </a>
   <span class="mw-editsection-bracket">
    ]
   </span>
  </span>
 </h2>
 <p>
  In the process of containerizing products, Micro Focus is defining usage standards in the following areas: container OS, images and engines, repositories and delivery.
 </p>
 <h3>
  <span class="mw-headline" id="Container_OS_Standard">
   Container OS Standard
  </span>
  <span class="mw-editsection">
   <span class="mw-editsection-bracket">
    [
   </span>
   <a class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-4" title="Edit section: ">
    edit
   </a>
   <span class="mw-editsection-divider">
    |
   </span>
   <a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-4" title="Edit section: ">
    edit source
   </a>
   <span class="mw-editsection-bracket">
    ]
   </span>
  </span>
 </h3>
 <p>
  <a class="image" onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);">
   <img alt="cdferwp201801 image5.png" data-file-height="690" data-file-width="1980" height="314" src="/mediawiki/images/thumb/8/83/cdferwp201801_image5.png/900px-cdferwp201801_image5.png" srcset="/mediawiki/images/thumb/8/83/cdferwp201801_image5.png/1350px-cdferwp201801_image5.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/thumb/8/83/cdferwp201801_image5.png/1800px-cdferwp201801_image5.png 2x" width="900"/>
  </a>
 </p>
 <p>
  openSUSE is our container OS base layer due to its relatively small size, support by a commercial entity, alignment with our host OS strategy.
 </p>
 <h3>
  <span class="mw-headline" id="Images_Standard">
   Images Standard
  </span>
  <span class="mw-editsection">
   <span class="mw-editsection-bracket">
    [
   </span>
   <a class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-5" title="Edit section: ">
    edit
   </a>
   <span class="mw-editsection-divider">
    |
   </span>
   <a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-5" title="Edit section: ">
    edit source
   </a>
   <span class="mw-editsection-bracket">
    ]
   </span>
  </span>
 </h3>
 <p>
  A consistent set of best practices for how to build a lean and quality container image have been defined along with support policy for Docker engine versions, both open source and Enterprise Edition.
 </p>
 <h3>
  <span class="mw-headline" id="Container_Image_Registry_Standard">
   Container Image Registry Standard
  </span>
  <span class="mw-editsection">
   <span class="mw-editsection-bracket">
    [
   </span>
   <a class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-6" title="Edit section: ">
    edit
   </a>
   <span class="mw-editsection-divider">
    |
   </span>
   <a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-6" title="Edit section: ">
    edit source
   </a>
   <span class="mw-editsection-bracket">
    ]
   </span>
  </span>
 </h3>
 <p>
  All container images are stored in Docker Hub for internal and external usages as primary repository.
 </p>
 <p>
  Customers can run their own private copy of the registry. An on-premise installation of an ITOM Suite brings an embedded registry inside the Kubernetes cluster.
 </p>
 <p>
  Cloud-based installations can be configured to use either the embedded registry, a cloud-vendor provided registry instance or an in-cloud private customer managed registry instance.
 </p>
 <h3>
  <span class="mw-headline" id="Delivery_Standard">
   Delivery Standard
  </span>
  <span class="mw-editsection">
   <span class="mw-editsection-bracket">
    [
   </span>
   <a class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-7" title="Edit section: ">
    edit
   </a>
   <span class="mw-editsection-divider">
    |
   </span>
   <a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-7" title="Edit section: ">
    edit source
   </a>
   <span class="mw-editsection-bracket">
    ]
   </span>
  </span>
 </h3>
 <p>
  For software products that are delivered through Docker Hub, a set of standards and best practices outline how to prepare for container publishing in aspects such as vulnerability scanning and cleaning, image structure best practices etc.
 </p>
